  "about": {
    "portrait": "assets/img/about.jpg",
    "body": [
      "I am a performing artist working across contemporary dance, kathak, yoga, physical theatre, and somatics. For the past ten years, dance has been at the heart of how I experience the world, understand my body, and connect with others.I enjoy experimenting, improvising, and creating movement that grows out of these practices and embodied experiences. My work moves between performing, choreography, direction, facilitation, and artistic research.",
      "My dance journey began at the age of 20 with Sadhya Dance Company, performing their repertory productions. Since 2018, I have been training in Kathak at Bharatiya Kala Kendra, Delhi. In 2020, I completed my Master's in Performance Practice (Dance) from Ambedkar University Delhi. It was here that my interest in interdisciplinary performance deepened and I became curious about how the body holds memory, knowledge, and imagination.",
      "As a choreographer, I am drawn to the complexities of human emotions, the inner world, absurdity, and the quiet strength that often goes unnoticed in everyday life. My choreographic works have been presented at Serendipity Arts Festival (2024) and India Art Fair (2025), and continue to evolve through reflecting and experimenting.",
      "I am also an active member of Khuli Khirkee (formerly Gati Dance Forum), a shared space for artists and practitioners that that continues to shape my practice through dialogue, collaboration, and exchange. Alongside performing and choreographing, I facilitate movement workshops and community classes, creating inclusive spaces where people can reconnect with their bodies through curiosity and joy."
    ]
  },
